# Internationalization (en / fa / zh)

## File layout (mkdocs-static-i18n folder mode)

| Locale | Path |
|--------|------|
| English | `docs/en/.../page.md` |
| Persian (RTL) | `docs/fa/.../page.md` |
| Chinese | `docs/zh/.../page.md` |

Logical keys (inventory, YAML) are **relative to `docs/en/`** — e.g. `cheatsheet/cli/rgw`.

Use `scripts/i18n.py` helpers: `locale_path()`, `write_localized()` (English base must live under `docs/en/`).

## Content tiers

| Tier | Examples | FA/ZH strategy |
|------|----------|----------------|
| Hand-written | `docs/en/cheatsheet/cli/`, guides prose, `index.md` | Translate in `scripts/locales/pages/*.yaml` or edit `docs/fa/…` / `docs/zh/…` directly |
| Generated guides | `guides/rgw-config/`, `guides/osd-config/` | `generate-*-guide.py` writes all locale trees |
| Config tables | `config/<subsystem>/*.md` | English only under `docs/en/`; `config/OVERVIEW` gets fa/zh wrappers |
| Architecture | `docs/en/arch/rgw/` | `sync-rgw-from-docs-extended.py` + locale YAML |

## Section hub parity

`docs/{en,fa,zh}/cheatsheet/index.md`, `arch/index.md`, `dev/index.md` must share **identical HTML structure**; only text and RTL arrow direction differ.

Excluded from `sync-i18n-pages.py` `HAND_PAGES` (manual only).

**Mandatory workflow when any locale file changes:** see `.cursor/rules/doc-locale-parity.mdc`.

## Sync commands

```bash
python3 scripts/sync-i18n-pages.py    # HAND_PAGES prose
python3 scripts/sync-i18n-config.py   # config/OVERVIEW fa/zh
python3 scripts/regenerate-docs.py    # includes both + generators
```

## Inventory & human review

```bash
python3 scripts/generate-content-inventory.py
```

Mark human-reviewed pages in `scripts/data/content-review.yaml` (key = path under `docs/en/` without `.md`).

## Do not

- Re-add section `index` pages to `HAND_PAGES` (stale YAML in `home.yaml` would overwrite hubs)
- Use `.fa.md` / `.zh.md` suffix files — folder layout only
- Treat fa/zh with `fallback_page_note` or `upstream_table_note` as fully translated
- Translate CLI flag names or `<placeholders>` — see `cheatsheet/guides/cli-style-guide.md`
